Description: Building upon the Dirichlet-multinomial regression framework, we develop an high-dimensional Bayesian hierarchical model for microbiota analysis that exploits subject-specific regression coefficients to simultaneously borrow strength across districts and include complex interactions between diet and clinical factors if supported by the data.
